WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:24.566 --> 00:00:25.525
Mr. Governor!

3
00:00:25.608 --> 00:00:28.236
-Good to see you.
-Thank you. Go ahead. sir.

4
00:00:28.319 --> 00:00:30.655
-Welcome back.
-The governor's here?

5
00:00:30.739 --> 00:00:32.407
Mr. Governor!

6
00:00:32.490 --> 00:00:33.742
Congratulations!

7
00:00:36.494 --> 00:00:39.247
You work so hard. Thank you all very much.

8
00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:40.915
Thank you.

9
00:00:40.999 --> 00:00:44.210
As you know. the most important speech
is the one I'll give tomorrow.

10
00:00:44.294 --> 00:00:45.545
Let's make it count!

11
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:49.174
The election is upon us. Two more days.

12
00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:51.301
It's the final push.

13
00:00:51.384 --> 00:00:53.803
Let's keep it up and put on a show!

14
00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:56.056
Yeah!

15
00:01:29.464 --> 00:01:30.673
Kaho. hey!

16
00:01:31.216 --> 00:01:33.051
Hey! You okay? Are you hurt?

17
00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:36.596
But just look over there. Look.

18
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:57.158
Go check inside!

19
00:01:57.242 --> 00:01:58.743
I'm fine! Go check inside!

20
00:01:58.827 --> 00:01:59.953
Right away!

21
00:02:00.036 --> 00:02:01.955
You okay?

22
00:02:04.290 --> 00:02:06.918
We should get out of here.
Come on. let's go.

23
00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:12.298
Breaking news.

24
00:02:12.382 --> 00:02:14.634
The Metropolitan Police Department
is reporting

25
00:02:14.717 --> 00:02:19.556
that the Human Vapor has attacked
Governor Miura's campaign office in Tokyo.

26
00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:22.016
Three have been reported dead
in the attack.

27
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:25.728
with multiple others injured.
some in critical condition.

28
00:02:26.229 --> 00:02:30.859
Governor Miura was in the headquarters
at the time and was injured in the attack…

29
00:02:30.942 --> 00:02:33.736
Miura ordered the Human Vapor
to attack us.

30
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:36.573
He's the reason my brother's dead.

31
00:02:37.115 --> 00:02:38.533
I just don't…

32
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:42.120
Why would he do that?

33
00:02:42.620 --> 00:02:43.746
I don't get it.

34
00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:45.290
…five more dead…

35
00:02:45.373 --> 00:02:47.959
He was ordering
the Human Vapor's attacks.

36
00:02:48.751 --> 00:02:51.045
So then. who put the hit out on him?

37
00:02:57.218 --> 00:02:59.596
Wait. Fujita's camera is still…

38
00:03:01.389 --> 00:03:03.808
We were trying to find out
the Human Vapor's identity.

39
00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:05.351
He set up a camera!

40
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:09.147
It would still be there.
and it should still be working.

41
00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:12.400
It might've caught the person
who ordered the attack on Miura.

42
00:03:23.536 --> 00:03:24.787
-Is he okay?
-What's going on?

43
00:03:24.871 --> 00:03:25.914
I don't like this.

44
00:03:43.806 --> 00:03:44.807
What now?

45
00:03:46.768 --> 00:03:47.977
Gimme a second.

46
00:03:54.609 --> 00:03:55.443
Huh?

47
00:03:57.695 --> 00:04:00.323
-Hey.
-What do you want. huh?

48
00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:03.618
-You fuckin' deaf?
-Get outta here!

49
00:04:03.701 --> 00:04:05.453
Where you goin'?

50
00:04:06.579 --> 00:04:08.665
Hey. I asked you a question. brother!

51
00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:22.762
Through here.

52
00:04:36.693 --> 00:04:38.069
The coast is clear.

53
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:40.780
He'll be back soon. We have to hurry.

54
00:04:41.781 --> 00:04:43.449
Where'd Fujita put the camera?

55
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:45.618
This way. I think.

56
00:05:01.134 --> 00:05:04.470
In about two hours' time.
I need you for something.

57
00:05:04.554 --> 00:05:08.766
There will be a number of volunteers
at Takeshi Miura's campaign headquarters.

58
00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:10.226
That's your target.

59
00:05:11.352 --> 00:05:13.271
Kill three people there.

60
00:05:13.354 --> 00:05:14.188
After that.

61
00:05:14.272 --> 00:05:18.109
I need you to kill all the homeless people
in front of the station.

62
00:05:18.192 --> 00:05:20.028
Leave none of them alive.

63
00:05:20.111 --> 00:05:21.237
And one more thing.

64
00:05:23.239 --> 00:05:24.532
Don't kill me.

65
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:28.369
This guy is just the worst.

66
00:05:29.370 --> 00:05:32.665
This station
insists on reporting about Human Vapor.

67
00:05:32.749 --> 00:05:34.709
all day. every day.

68
00:05:34.792 --> 00:05:36.753
You are terrifying all the voters.

69
00:05:36.836 --> 00:05:40.715
so now more and more of them
are calling for Miura to be reelected.

70
00:05:44.218 --> 00:05:46.512
An attack in downtown Tokyo.

71
00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:51.351
and yet Miura's approval rating is
just gonna keep going up.

72
00:05:52.685 --> 00:05:53.519
What?

73
00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:59.567
In the wake of an attack or a tragedy.
we all hope for stability.

74
00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:03.905
The governor
only stands to benefit from this.

75
00:06:06.324 --> 00:06:08.117
Wait. what are you saying?

76
00:06:08.201 --> 00:06:09.744
People are afraid.

77
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.705
An unstoppable force kills again.

78
00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:15.083
and no one knows what to do.

79
00:06:15.833 --> 00:06:18.294
But if Miura stands strong and leads.

80
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:21.589
he'll be seen as a hero.
He'll win by a landslide.

81
00:06:23.758 --> 00:06:26.344
So you're saying
in order to win the election.

82
00:06:28.262 --> 00:06:30.264
he condemned his own staff to die?

83
00:06:31.682 --> 00:06:33.476
Is that really surprising though?

84
00:06:34.102 --> 00:06:36.187
We know he doesn't value life. don't we?

85
00:06:39.982 --> 00:06:41.859
People are worthless to him.

86
00:06:45.071 --> 00:06:47.240
We're nothing but human fuel.

87
00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:52.120
Hey. Hey!

88
00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:54.956
There's someone inside.

89
00:06:58.835 --> 00:06:59.836
Hmm?

90
00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:05.091
Let's go.

91
00:07:07.802 --> 00:07:09.011
Wait. wait!

92
00:07:11.597 --> 00:07:12.890
I have an idea.

93
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:23.693
You.

94
00:07:23.776 --> 00:07:25.736
What do you think you're doing?

95
00:07:26.863 --> 00:07:28.239
What was that? Get him!

96
00:07:28.322 --> 00:07:29.949
Kaito. get me some chain.

97
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:38.499
Get him! He's just one guy!

98
00:07:43.254 --> 00:07:45.006
-Hurry. Kaho.
-Okay.

99
00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:11.574
What the hell did you do?

100
00:08:11.657 --> 00:08:13.326
Is he dead? Oh shit.

101
00:08:31.636 --> 00:08:34.680
The world will soon know my true power.

102
00:08:35.932 --> 00:08:39.227
The world will soon know my true power.

103
00:08:40.394 --> 00:08:44.607
The world will soon know my true power.

104
00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:05.086
Hello?

105
00:09:05.169 --> 00:09:08.130
Hey. Um. we've run into a complication.

106
00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:10.216
What happened? Where are you?

107
00:09:10.716 --> 00:09:12.093
The abandoned warehouse.

108
00:09:12.593 --> 00:09:14.470
We think they taped the whole thing.

109
00:09:15.304 --> 00:09:17.390
What? What thing?

110
00:09:18.599 --> 00:09:20.685
You gave an order to the Vapor guy.

111
00:09:21.936 --> 00:09:22.937
You did. right?

112
00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:26.649
And while you were doing that.
you were secretly being recorded.

113
00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:30.820
Where's the footage?

114
00:09:33.281 --> 00:09:34.532
Don't know.

115
00:09:34.615 --> 00:09:37.910
A detective called Okamoto was here
with the video camera.

116
00:09:37.994 --> 00:09:39.453
We caught him. He's with us.

117
00:09:39.954 --> 00:09:42.498
I need to know where that recording went.

118
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:45.167
Ask him. but keep him alive.

119
00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:49.338
Will do.
We'll get the info. Leave it to us.

120
00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:50.840
And don't do anything…

121
00:10:28.544 --> 00:10:31.339
You don't have to worry about that
at least.

122
00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:34.300
You've pulled ahead of Kirishima. Up 7%.

123
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:37.136
We've got this in the bag. sir.

124
00:10:38.179 --> 00:10:40.306
Be that as it may. it's not over.

125
00:10:40.389 --> 00:10:43.309
We'll cement our lead tomorrow
any way we can.

126
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:01.077
You wanna talk yet?

127
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:03.371
Just tell us where the recording ended up.

128
00:11:03.454 --> 00:11:05.748
Where did you put it?

129
00:11:11.837 --> 00:11:14.924
You really need to start talking.

130
00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:17.051
I promised I'd keep you alive.

131
00:11:17.134 --> 00:11:19.178
but I've never been keen on promises.

132
00:11:19.261 --> 00:11:21.555
Where's the fun in that?

133
00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:42.952
Just fuckin' tell us!

134
00:11:43.452 --> 00:11:44.995
You listening?

135
00:11:46.914 --> 00:11:49.333
-Where is the recording?
-Hey!

136
00:11:51.794 --> 00:11:54.964
Let's all just take a breath.
You've gone too far.

137
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:57.550
Look what you did.

138
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:03.931
You're just like your father.
The spitting image.

139
00:12:04.014 --> 00:12:06.892
Huh? Down to your fat little baby cheeks.

140
00:12:07.893 --> 00:12:10.730
-So what did you find out?
-Nothing.

141
00:12:12.815 --> 00:12:14.775
-Gimme that.
-Huh?

142
00:12:17.778 --> 00:12:19.613
What the hell?

143
00:12:22.324 --> 00:12:23.325
Sada.

144
00:12:25.453 --> 00:12:26.704
Sada?

145
00:12:30.082 --> 00:12:32.752
Okamoto? Am I saying that right?

146
00:12:35.671 --> 00:12:37.256
Great to meet you.

147
00:12:37.923 --> 00:12:40.801
I'm Miura. governor of Tokyo.

148
00:12:42.178 --> 00:12:44.555
I thought

149
00:12:45.264 --> 00:12:46.932
you were with Mufu.

150
00:12:48.809 --> 00:12:50.770
Such a pathetic organization.

151
00:12:58.152 --> 00:12:59.862
Very well.

152
00:13:03.657 --> 00:13:07.203
I wanna tell you a story
I heard once in Romania.

153
00:13:10.831 --> 00:13:14.084
Miguel was a lovely. carefree young man…

154
00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:19.757
whose life's work was running a bee farm.

155
00:13:21.008 --> 00:13:23.093
The hell are you talking about?

156
00:13:24.136 --> 00:13:25.387
Every bee

157
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:29.099
has its own role in the colony.

158
00:13:30.768 --> 00:13:32.770
The bees who defend the hive

159
00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:35.481
and those who make honey.

160
00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:38.818
But every single one…

161
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:42.947
works. lives.
and gives its life to the queen bee.

162
00:13:46.283 --> 00:13:48.577
The queen has a big task.

163
00:13:50.454 --> 00:13:51.914
She mates.

164
00:13:52.456 --> 00:13:55.000
expands their numbers. and grows the hive.

165
00:13:56.126 --> 00:13:57.628
And humans

166
00:13:58.796 --> 00:14:01.340
have exactly the same roles.

167
00:14:02.925 --> 00:14:05.135
From the moment you're born.

168
00:14:06.762 --> 00:14:10.057
your life becomes one of work
for a great machine.

169
00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:12.643
You live and die as its fuel.

170
00:14:16.981 --> 00:14:19.108
Do you understand now?

171
00:14:19.608 --> 00:14:21.527
We need the fuel.

172
00:14:22.027 --> 00:14:24.822
We need the human fuel.

173
00:14:28.909 --> 00:14:32.079
Of course. a great machine needs
great people to run it.

174
00:14:32.162 --> 00:14:33.539
Don't you agree?

175
00:14:36.208 --> 00:14:39.879
And you actually think
you're one of those great people?

176
00:14:40.629 --> 00:14:42.840
That's such a fucking joke!

177
00:14:42.923 --> 00:14:46.594
Your machine is nothing.
and you're living in a fantasy world.

178
00:14:49.179 --> 00:14:51.140
Look.

179
00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:58.439
Since you asked so nicely.

180
00:14:58.939 --> 00:15:01.275
I'll tell you what part you have to play.

181
00:15:01.358 --> 00:15:03.235
You're going to stand beside me.

182
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:05.821
I need a new right hand.

183
00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:07.865
now that Sakamoto's dead.

184
00:15:10.951 --> 00:15:13.996
Together. we'll conquer the world.

185
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:22.004
Ugh!

186
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:28.302
Such spirit.

187
00:15:29.386 --> 00:15:30.721
That's too bad.

188
00:15:31.889 --> 00:15:33.599
Tell me who has the footage.

189
00:15:34.099 --> 00:15:36.560
You didn't come here alone. did you?

190
00:15:40.356 --> 00:15:42.358
Start talking.

191
00:15:43.817 --> 00:15:45.402
You have five seconds.

192
00:15:49.281 --> 00:15:51.617
Five. Time to breathe.

193
00:15:51.700 --> 00:15:54.203
Four. Breathe in.

194
00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:56.956
Three. Breathe out.

195
00:15:58.540 --> 00:16:00.042
Two. Time's up.

196
00:16:00.125 --> 00:16:03.045
Okay! Wait! I'll tell you!
I'll tell you what you wanna know.

197
00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:07.633
I'll just… I need a second to breathe.

198
00:16:07.716 --> 00:16:09.343
Where is it?

199
00:16:09.426 --> 00:16:11.595
Where the hell is it?

200
00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:17.643
You're too late.

201
00:16:20.938 --> 00:16:23.399
Kyoko Kono. She has it now.

202
00:16:23.899 --> 00:16:25.067
She's long gone.

203
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:29.738
She's going to air it.

204
00:16:30.239 --> 00:16:31.824
All the networks will.

205
00:16:35.327 --> 00:16:36.787
You won't win.

206
00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:41.083
You're done. Kai.

207
00:16:42.292 --> 00:16:43.460
That's what you think.

208
00:16:49.216 --> 00:16:51.218
I've got an ace in the hole.

209
00:16:52.428 --> 00:16:53.679
Kai!

210
00:16:55.597 --> 00:16:58.308
No matter what happens. I'll stop you.

211
00:16:58.809 --> 00:17:01.395
I'll make you pay
for everything you've done!

212
00:17:03.981 --> 00:17:06.191
I'll make you pay!

213
00:17:15.659 --> 00:17:19.038
Shut up! Don't you ever stop talking?
Just shut up!

214
00:17:28.338 --> 00:17:29.548
Listener.

215
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:32.384
please.

216
00:17:33.594 --> 00:17:35.262
make a wish.

217
00:17:38.140 --> 00:17:39.516
I want you

218
00:17:40.059 --> 00:17:43.353
to find Kyoko Kono
and the footage she took from here.

219
00:17:43.896 --> 00:17:45.856
Make sure the data's destroyed.

220
00:17:45.939 --> 00:17:47.608
then I want you to kill Ms. Kono.

221
00:17:56.158 --> 00:18:00.370
Mr. Okamoto knows too much.
Do whatever you want with him.

222
00:18:03.248 --> 00:18:05.167
-Get him up.
-You got it.

223
00:18:05.667 --> 00:18:07.086
♪ Ellie ♪

224
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:08.837
♪ My love ♪

225
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:10.297
♪ So sweet… ♪

226
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:15.469
That's your target.
Kill three people there.

227
00:18:15.552 --> 00:18:18.305
-After that…
-This guy's just the worst.

228
00:18:20.349 --> 00:18:22.559
Hey. Hey!

229
00:18:23.685 --> 00:18:25.354
There's someone inside.

230
00:18:28.148 --> 00:18:29.024
Hmm?

231
00:18:30.651 --> 00:18:31.819
Let's go.

232
00:18:33.403 --> 00:18:34.655
Wait. wait!

233
00:18:36.031 --> 00:18:37.241
I have an idea.

234
00:18:39.118 --> 00:18:40.619
Kaho and I will get outta here.

235
00:18:40.702 --> 00:18:43.080
get the video out to the public
as soon as we can.

236
00:18:43.831 --> 00:18:45.499
What I need from you. Kenji…

237
00:18:45.999 --> 00:18:49.628
Can you figure out some way
to make Miura send Ren after me?

238
00:18:50.921 --> 00:18:52.881
You can't be serious.
If I do that. you'll--

239
00:18:52.965 --> 00:18:53.966
Trust me.

240
00:18:55.092 --> 00:18:56.385
I can do this.

241
00:18:57.136 --> 00:18:59.179
I know exactly how to stop him.

242
00:19:01.932 --> 00:19:02.933
How. Kyoko?

243
00:19:07.396 --> 00:19:09.523
We have to end this before he kills again.

244
00:19:10.941 --> 00:19:12.025
Okay?

245
00:19:13.527 --> 00:19:15.154
Please. trust me.

246
00:19:39.219 --> 00:19:40.679
Parfinee time.

247
00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:27.267
HUMAN VAPOR

248
00:20:34.608 --> 00:20:40.614
TOKYO GOVERNOR CANDIDATE
KAZUMI KIRISHIMA

249
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:51.250
There she is.

250
00:21:05.722 --> 00:21:07.057
Hey. Kaho.

251
00:21:07.975 --> 00:21:09.351
It's gonna be all right.

252
00:21:16.191 --> 00:21:17.025
Okay.

253
00:21:19.361 --> 00:21:20.654
Right. I'm going in.

254
00:22:58.001 --> 00:23:00.045
It's the day
before the election.

255
00:23:00.545 --> 00:23:01.880
We've had our ups and downs.

256
00:23:01.963 --> 00:23:04.549
but let's do our best
and fight until the very end.

257
00:23:05.050 --> 00:23:07.177
-I'm counting on you!
-Yes. ma'am!

258
00:23:11.223 --> 00:23:12.474
Excuse me…

259
00:23:14.059 --> 00:23:14.976
Sorry. hello?

260
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:18.230
Pardon the interruption. Ms. Kirishima.

261
00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:20.273
I. um…

262
00:23:20.774 --> 00:23:22.734
My name's Kaho Fujikawa.

263
00:23:23.235 --> 00:23:26.822
I'm… a video streamer
and I. uh. would like to…

264
00:23:26.905 --> 00:23:30.033
If it's possible to speak to Ms. Kirishima
just for a few minutes?

265
00:23:30.117 --> 00:23:32.077
I have some questions for her.
Is that okay?

266
00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:35.080
This isn't a good time.
We're about to go to a rally.

267
00:23:35.163 --> 00:23:36.790
Wait. wait! Hang on!

268
00:23:36.873 --> 00:23:37.999
It's about Miura!

269
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:39.876
-Miss. I'm sorry. but…
-It's important.

270
00:23:44.756 --> 00:23:47.801
Bag it.

271
00:23:47.884 --> 00:23:51.513
We're seizing anything related
to the case of the Human Vapor.

272
00:23:51.596 --> 00:23:53.515
Got it.

273
00:23:53.598 --> 00:23:55.308
Okay. now the laptop.

274
00:23:58.395 --> 00:24:00.063
KONO

275
00:24:05.360 --> 00:24:06.945
I'm alone. Where have you been?

276
00:24:07.028 --> 00:24:11.324
Tatsuya. you told me you wanted
to be a journalist no matter what.

277
00:24:12.367 --> 00:24:14.035
-I did.
-Then listen.

278
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:17.497
I'm gonna send you something important.
Get it on the air. now.

279
00:24:17.998 --> 00:24:20.750
What? You want me to what?

280
00:25:23.939 --> 00:25:25.273
It is time…

281
00:25:27.317 --> 00:25:29.986
for the Parfinee. Prepare yourselves.

282
00:25:30.570 --> 00:25:31.863
Yes. boss.

283
00:25:44.876 --> 00:25:48.588
Now. where to begin?

284
00:25:52.842 --> 00:25:56.263
Wow. You have such pretty eyes.

285
00:25:59.683 --> 00:26:02.394
We'll leave those pretty eyes
for the very end.

286
00:26:03.019 --> 00:26:04.521
How's that sound?

287
00:26:13.280 --> 00:26:15.657
I'll start with the ears instead.

288
00:26:26.626 --> 00:26:29.045
How many cuts will it take?

289
00:26:29.129 --> 00:26:30.880
Should we start from the top?

290
00:26:34.926 --> 00:26:37.178
On second thought. let's do the bottom.

291
00:27:13.381 --> 00:27:15.592
Who's next?

292
00:27:48.416 --> 00:27:51.378
Tell me what a Parfinee is. you asshole.

293
00:28:31.584 --> 00:28:34.879
…a number of volunteers
at Takeshi Miura's campaign headquarters.

294
00:28:34.963 --> 00:28:36.381
That's your target.

295
00:28:37.006 --> 00:28:39.008
-Kill three people there.
-What?

296
00:28:39.092 --> 00:28:41.094
Is this recording real?

297
00:28:41.761 --> 00:28:43.012
Yeah. I assure you.

298
00:28:43.513 --> 00:28:45.598
This should be enough
to stop him for good.

299
00:28:45.682 --> 00:28:47.225
You have to go public with it.

300
00:28:47.308 --> 00:28:49.436
There's not enough time
to prove it's real.

301
00:28:50.186 --> 00:28:52.564
It's political suicide
if it turns out to be fake.

302
00:28:52.647 --> 00:28:55.859
You'll be run out not just of the election
but politics forever.

303
00:28:56.359 --> 00:28:59.904
Miss. I have to insist you leave. Now.

304
00:28:59.988 --> 00:29:01.489
Come along. miss.

305
00:29:05.285 --> 00:29:07.370
-Hang on!
-Just leave. please.

306
00:29:07.454 --> 00:29:10.373
No. stop! Are you trying
to win the election or aren't you?

307
00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:14.085
-Kirishima is trailing…
-You're polling behind him. right?

308
00:29:16.838 --> 00:29:20.008
She's right.
We can't win unless something changes.

309
00:29:24.554 --> 00:29:26.097
Let's bet it all on this video.

310
00:29:28.933 --> 00:29:31.227
We can release it on our channel
right away.

311
00:29:32.645 --> 00:29:35.523
No. no. Ms. Kirishima. please reconsider.
It's not a good idea.

312
00:29:35.607 --> 00:29:36.775
After what you just saw.

313
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:39.110
you're telling me you want us
to stay silent

314
00:29:39.194 --> 00:29:41.154
when he's killing his own constituents?

315
00:29:41.237 --> 00:29:43.907
I think someone else
should release the video first.

316
00:29:43.990 --> 00:29:46.367
We can't afford to wait!

317
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:48.203
We'll leak it to the media!

318
00:29:48.286 --> 00:29:51.080
No one would touch this
the day before an election!

319
00:29:55.877 --> 00:29:58.213
I can stream the video. on my channel.

320
00:30:03.051 --> 00:30:06.638
And once it's out.
all you'd have to do is repost it.

321
00:30:15.980 --> 00:30:17.357
-I've got more copies.
-Great.

322
00:30:17.440 --> 00:30:19.567
-This is wild.
-You got that right.

323
00:30:19.651 --> 00:30:20.985
Gruesome stuff.

324
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:22.821
"Radiation."

325
00:30:23.488 --> 00:30:25.949
-What are you doing?
-Oh. Director.

326
00:30:26.533 --> 00:30:28.910
All this material was sent to us by Kyoko.

327
00:30:28.993 --> 00:30:29.994
What?

328
00:30:31.496 --> 00:30:33.790
-When was this?
-Just now. by email.

329
00:30:33.873 --> 00:30:36.918
-The Human Vapor. There he is.
-What?

330
00:30:41.631 --> 00:30:43.508
Ren Tsutsumida.

331
00:30:43.591 --> 00:30:45.718
-Ren Tsutsumida.
-Ren Tsutsumida.

332
00:30:53.643 --> 00:30:54.644
Hello?

333
00:30:54.727 --> 00:30:55.812
Miura. he…

334
00:30:55.895 --> 00:30:58.356
he sent the Human Vapor out to kill you.

335
00:30:58.439 --> 00:31:00.108
Is he there?

336
00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:02.402
Thankfully. not yet.

337
00:31:02.902 --> 00:31:04.571
The video will be online real soon.

338
00:31:05.989 --> 00:31:08.575
Kyoko. where are you?

339
00:31:09.742 --> 00:31:11.828
I'm heading
to the old JNT building.

340
00:31:12.537 --> 00:31:14.122
I'll lure Ren there and stop him.

341
00:31:14.956 --> 00:31:17.917
Yeah. all right. I'll meet you there.

342
00:31:18.501 --> 00:31:19.544
Kenji.

343
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:22.797
You're gonna bring Miura to justice.
won't you?

344
00:31:23.673 --> 00:31:24.674
What?

345
00:31:27.635 --> 00:31:29.429
Get revenge for all of us.

346
00:31:30.555 --> 00:31:32.140
It's all up to you now.

347
00:31:35.894 --> 00:31:37.103
Kyoko.

348
00:31:42.817 --> 00:31:44.027
Please. Kenji.

349
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:04.047
First of all. I need to thank you
for coming out to our final rally.

350
00:32:04.130 --> 00:32:05.882
TAKESHI MIURA
LOVE. LOVE

351
00:32:05.965 --> 00:32:07.717
Thank you so much!

352
00:32:09.260 --> 00:32:13.306
And now. the moment
you've all been waiting so patiently for.

353
00:32:13.389 --> 00:32:15.016
-On this final day…
-Takeshi!

354
00:32:15.099 --> 00:32:17.602
…we'd love for you
to hear one last time

355
00:32:17.685 --> 00:32:19.646
from the current Governor of Tokyo.

356
00:32:19.729 --> 00:32:23.066
Let's hear it for Takeshi Miura!

357
00:32:26.277 --> 00:32:28.488
My friends.
I've been through hell.

358
00:32:29.405 --> 00:32:31.741
And I'm back. stronger than ever!

359
00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:39.832
Let us keep our dreams alive!

360
00:33:11.364 --> 00:33:13.408
This one's for you. Fujita.

361
00:33:17.078 --> 00:33:20.206
And three. two. one.

362
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:25.461
Welcome to horror paradise!

363
00:33:25.545 --> 00:33:27.714
So what's up. killers? Are you ready?

364
00:33:28.464 --> 00:33:30.133
I know what you're thinking.

365
00:33:30.216 --> 00:33:32.635
"Who's that girl? I know that voice."

366
00:33:32.719 --> 00:33:34.846
Oh! It's me!

367
00:33:34.929 --> 00:33:38.057
I'm Kaho. Fujita's sister!
So good to meet all of you!

368
00:33:38.141 --> 00:33:40.226
It's my first time
on this side of the camera.

369
00:33:40.309 --> 00:33:41.728
I'm sure you can tell.

370
00:33:41.811 --> 00:33:42.895
LIVE

371
00:33:42.979 --> 00:33:47.775
So. not only will today's live stream
be a memorial for our boy

372
00:33:47.859 --> 00:33:51.487
and my sweet. dear. nerdy brother Fujita.

373
00:33:51.988 --> 00:33:55.867
but we'll also be airing explosive footage
of the Human Vapor.

374
00:33:55.950 --> 00:33:58.161
Smash that like button and share!

375
00:33:58.244 --> 00:34:01.080
Ready. killers? Here we go.

376
00:34:01.789 --> 00:34:03.958
This is super-exclusive footage.

377
00:34:04.042 --> 00:34:08.671
brought to you by none other
than our own god of fear and pain.

378
00:34:08.755 --> 00:34:12.258
He gave his life for you!

379
00:34:14.635 --> 00:34:17.221
We've accomplished much
in such a short time.

380
00:34:17.305 --> 00:34:20.892
Over the past four years.
crime has dropped by 10%.

381
00:34:21.392 --> 00:34:25.438
and homelessness in the city
has been cut very nearly in half!

382
00:34:28.316 --> 00:34:29.984
Thank you so much!

383
00:34:30.943 --> 00:34:32.695
We couldn't have done it without you!

384
00:34:32.779 --> 00:34:34.197
And that's not all!

385
00:34:34.280 --> 00:34:37.200
To help stabilize the falling birthrate.

386
00:34:38.201 --> 00:34:40.620
no more waiting lists for daycare!

387
00:34:45.291 --> 00:34:49.504
For households with two or more children.
my government…

388
00:34:51.547 --> 00:34:53.716
…will provide. per month.

389
00:34:53.800 --> 00:34:55.510
50.000 yen for child allowance!

390
00:34:55.593 --> 00:34:57.845
Wait. what?

391
00:34:57.929 --> 00:35:00.556
And today I am proud to announce

392
00:35:00.640 --> 00:35:03.810
that we will make university tuition
free as well!

393
00:35:03.893 --> 00:35:05.061
So.

394
00:35:05.603 --> 00:35:08.856
these three measures
will be the basis of our governance.

395
00:35:08.940 --> 00:35:11.984
The people of Tokyo
will have what they crave…

396
00:35:12.068 --> 00:35:14.320
GOVERNOR MIURA ACCUSED IN VIDEO

397
00:35:15.154 --> 00:35:17.031
I… We won't stop!

398
00:35:17.115 --> 00:35:18.825
THERE SHOULD BE VOLUNTEER STAFF

399
00:35:20.284 --> 00:35:22.245
WREAK HAVOC
KILL THREE PEOPLE

400
00:35:23.538 --> 00:35:24.914
Until all of us…

401
00:35:29.752 --> 00:35:32.672
Is this true?
Get the hell out of here! We trusted you!

402
00:35:32.755 --> 00:35:34.423
He's not worth it.

403
00:35:34.507 --> 00:35:36.384
Please. everybody! Please!

404
00:35:36.467 --> 00:35:39.470
We believed in you!
Get the hell out!

405
00:35:39.554 --> 00:35:41.514
You lied to all of us!

406
00:35:41.597 --> 00:35:43.891
"MY BROTHER SACRIFICED HIMSELF"

407
00:35:43.975 --> 00:35:45.977
What's going on?

408
00:35:48.396 --> 00:35:51.566
You! Come here! You wanna tell me
what the hell is going on?!

409
00:35:51.649 --> 00:35:52.984
Let's just take it easy.

410
00:35:53.067 --> 00:35:55.945
We'll head back and figure something out.
Sound good?

411
00:36:15.756 --> 00:36:18.509
It's got
a shocking number of views already.

412
00:36:18.593 --> 00:36:22.138
Your style's a little unorthodox.
but it certainly works well.

413
00:36:22.221 --> 00:36:24.432
Okay. Well. thanks.

414
00:36:24.515 --> 00:36:26.350
Yeah. I… I appreciate it.

415
00:36:31.189 --> 00:36:32.815
-How's it looking?
-Fine.

416
00:36:33.649 --> 00:36:35.526
-Ready?
-I'm good to go.

417
00:36:37.278 --> 00:36:39.280
All right. then. In three…

418
00:36:42.742 --> 00:36:46.454
Hello. everyone. I'm sure most
of you know me. Kazumi Kirishima.

419
00:36:46.537 --> 00:36:49.498
This is an emergency live stream.

420
00:36:49.582 --> 00:36:52.501
I imagine by now. many of you
will have seen today's stream

421
00:36:52.585 --> 00:36:55.129
from Fujita and Kaho's Horror Zone.

422
00:36:56.464 --> 00:36:59.508
It's hard to believe.
I know I have trouble believing it…

423
00:37:41.676 --> 00:37:43.427
Excuse me. sir? Sir. hey!

424
00:37:44.929 --> 00:37:47.723
Stop!

425
00:37:54.563 --> 00:37:56.983
Hey. you're back! You all right?

426
00:37:57.066 --> 00:37:58.651
What happened? You're hurt.

427
00:37:58.734 --> 00:38:00.361
Hey! What's going on?

428
00:38:01.195 --> 00:38:02.697
Kenji. stop!

429
00:38:03.197 --> 00:38:04.907
Hey! Listen up!

430
00:38:05.533 --> 00:38:07.410
We're arresting Governor Miura.

431
00:38:07.493 --> 00:38:10.079
What? Listen to yourself. Kenji.

432
00:38:10.579 --> 00:38:12.248
You must be out of your mind.

433
00:38:12.331 --> 00:38:15.626
Coming in here covered in blood.
screaming about arresting the governor?

434
00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:17.295
Where the hell have you even been?

435
00:38:17.795 --> 00:38:19.672
You know what? It doesn't matter.

436
00:38:19.755 --> 00:38:22.383
Because it's your ex-girlfriend
who we're after.

437
00:38:22.883 --> 00:38:26.012
Just bring her here.
I'll arrest her myself.

438
00:38:27.096 --> 00:38:29.223
Wait. stop! Hey!

439
00:38:30.725 --> 00:38:33.853
The footage seems to show Governor Miura
allegedly giving the orders

440
00:38:33.936 --> 00:38:36.647
to have some of his campaign staff killed.

441
00:38:37.148 --> 00:38:39.108
MAN ALLEGED TO BE GOVERNOR MIURA

442
00:38:39.191 --> 00:38:41.402
In about two hours' time.

443
00:38:41.944 --> 00:38:43.654
I need you for something.

444
00:38:44.280 --> 00:38:48.993
There will be a number of volunteers
at Takeshi Miura's campaign headquarters.

445
00:38:49.076 --> 00:38:50.619
That's your target.

446
00:38:51.871 --> 00:38:53.748
Kill three people there.

447
00:38:53.831 --> 00:38:58.127
After that. I need you to kill all the
homeless people in front of the station.

448
00:38:58.627 --> 00:39:02.173
This video was released today
via live stream by Kaho Fujikawa.

449
00:39:02.256 --> 00:39:05.760
sister of the now-deceased streamer
Fujita Fujikawa.

450
00:39:05.843 --> 00:39:08.095
She claims the murders
committed by the Human Vapor

451
00:39:08.179 --> 00:39:11.432
at Miura's campaign headquarters
were ordered by the governor himself.

452
00:39:11.515 --> 00:39:13.601
-Get a warrant for Miura. now.
-Yes. sir!

453
00:39:13.684 --> 00:39:15.561
Just wait a second!

454
00:39:17.146 --> 00:39:19.023
You know that won't work.

455
00:39:21.108 --> 00:39:23.611
You think this is enough
for an arrest warrant?

456
00:39:24.195 --> 00:39:27.239
If we don't do anything.
there's a good chance Miura's gonna run.

457
00:39:27.323 --> 00:39:30.117
-You feel good about that. Chief?
-If you go after Miura…

458
00:39:31.660 --> 00:39:34.497
you better be ready
to face the consequences.

459
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:40.336
Oh. so what?
We should just let him get away?

460
00:39:56.227 --> 00:39:57.353
I'm going.

461
00:40:00.564 --> 00:40:01.857
I'm going with him.

462
00:40:04.985 --> 00:40:06.362
All right. let's move!

463
00:40:20.709 --> 00:40:24.463
-I didn't know that. wow.
-It's funny. There are 23 different kinds.

464
00:40:24.547 --> 00:40:26.215
-Twenty-three?
-Something like that.

465
00:40:50.573 --> 00:40:53.075
-Police! Where's the governor?
-You can't storm in!

466
00:40:53.159 --> 00:40:54.160
Warrant's in the mail.

467
00:40:54.243 --> 00:40:56.078
You're not getting away with this!

468
00:40:56.162 --> 00:40:58.372
-Warrant's coming. okay?
-You can't do this!

469
00:40:58.998 --> 00:40:59.999
Miura!

470
00:41:02.042 --> 00:41:03.544
Where is he?

471
00:41:04.044 --> 00:41:05.212
Right over there.

472
00:41:07.298 --> 00:41:09.175
Or at least he was a minute ago.

473
00:41:11.343 --> 00:41:13.762
Set up a perimeter. We gotta find him.

474
00:41:13.846 --> 00:41:15.806
-He's not getting away.
-Yes. sir!

475
00:41:15.890 --> 00:41:17.099
-I'll take the stairs.
-Yeah.

476
00:41:18.976 --> 00:41:22.313
After all this time. that's it?
It's over?

477
00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:27.776
I see.
So that's just the way it has to be.

478
00:41:29.612 --> 00:41:31.322
And there's no other way?

479
00:41:31.405 --> 00:41:33.991
I have been loyal for so long. I…

480
00:41:35.534 --> 00:41:36.535
Yes. sir.

481
00:41:37.411 --> 00:41:38.621
I understand.

482
00:42:06.815 --> 00:42:09.693
That makes me human fuel too. doesn't it?

483
00:42:10.653 --> 00:42:11.820
I see.

484
00:42:23.082 --> 00:42:25.417
-You go that way!
-I'll go with him.

485
00:42:26.043 --> 00:42:27.711
-You can check down there.
-Got it.

486
00:42:39.348 --> 00:42:41.392
-Get off me!
-Miura's on the roof!

487
00:42:44.562 --> 00:42:45.938
Motoyama?

488
00:42:46.564 --> 00:42:47.690
Motoyama. come in!

489
00:42:48.190 --> 00:42:51.860
-Go! I've got him!
-Let go of me! You can't do this to me!

490
00:42:57.074 --> 00:42:59.577
All right! Fine. fine! Just hang on.

491
00:43:00.286 --> 00:43:02.079
I'm not resisting. okay?

492
00:43:02.705 --> 00:43:05.374
I'm not resisting. You got me!
It's fine. just…

493
00:43:28.188 --> 00:43:30.816
Yoshida. We don't have to fight.

494
00:43:30.899 --> 00:43:31.942
Huh?

495
00:43:33.694 --> 00:43:35.904
Careful. you're getting cocky. Michiko.

496
00:43:43.579 --> 00:43:45.247
Hurry! Run!

497
00:44:22.618 --> 00:44:24.161
No! No. wait! Wait. wait!

498
00:44:43.555 --> 00:44:45.557
Motoyama! Hey! You okay?

499
00:44:45.641 --> 00:44:48.477
Yeah. yeah. I'm fine.
He's up there. Go! Hurry!

500
00:44:49.520 --> 00:44:51.897
Motoyama's down.
we need medics on the rooftop!

501
00:45:00.698 --> 00:45:02.116
Miura!

502
00:45:03.742 --> 00:45:06.328
Oh. Okamoto!

503
00:45:09.289 --> 00:45:11.041
What brings you up here?

504
00:45:14.002 --> 00:45:15.921
End of the line. Give it up.

505
00:45:18.590 --> 00:45:20.217
It's over. You're done.

506
00:45:32.438 --> 00:45:33.814
Okamoto.

507
00:45:35.941 --> 00:45:38.902
I met a man once. named Miguel.

508
00:45:42.156 --> 00:45:44.366
He was a musician. played in a band.

509
00:45:45.743 --> 00:45:47.661
He was pretty good too.

510
00:45:51.498 --> 00:45:52.583
Ah…

511
00:45:52.666 --> 00:45:54.585
This is gonna take way too long.

512
00:45:54.668 --> 00:45:55.502
See ya.

513
00:46:03.635 --> 00:46:06.638
Let go of me. dammit!
Stop it! Stop it!

514
00:46:06.722 --> 00:46:09.349
I'm not letting you
get away again.

515
00:46:13.270 --> 00:46:17.065
Let go of me! Hey! Let go. dammit!

516
00:46:33.874 --> 00:46:35.167
Unless

517
00:46:36.335 --> 00:46:38.045
you wanna come along?

518
00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:39.963
Well?

519
00:46:50.933 --> 00:46:53.310
Okamoto! We've got you!

520
00:46:53.393 --> 00:46:56.605
No! Shit! Stop. no!

521
00:46:57.147 --> 00:46:58.440
Let go of me!

522
00:47:00.150 --> 00:47:02.736
Dammit. I want to die!
Let go of me!

523
00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:05.030
What are you doing? Get off of me!

524
00:47:05.113 --> 00:47:10.035
Let go! Stop! You can't do this! Ah!

525
00:47:23.340 --> 00:47:28.595
DANGER
NO ENTRY

526
00:48:13.724 --> 00:48:14.933
MAIN POWER ROOM

527
00:49:33.929 --> 00:49:36.515
You have one new message.

528
00:49:37.766 --> 00:49:39.643
I'm so sorry. Kenji.

529
00:49:41.603 --> 00:49:43.230
I lied to you earlier.

530
00:49:45.482 --> 00:49:48.151
We can't stop Ren. It's impossible.

531
00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:51.446
But I'm going to lock him in a vault.

532
00:49:52.239 --> 00:49:54.658
The one in the basement
of the old JNT building.

533
00:49:55.867 --> 00:49:57.452
Whatever happens.

534
00:49:58.453 --> 00:50:00.539
don't let him out.

535
00:51:24.456 --> 00:51:27.459
The Human Vapor! This ends now!

536
00:52:14.131 --> 00:52:15.132
Ren.

537
00:52:17.759 --> 00:52:21.513
Can I make a wish please. Ren? Can I?

538
00:52:23.265 --> 00:52:25.016
Oh. of course you can.

539
00:52:26.768 --> 00:52:28.895
Go right ahead and make a wish.

540
00:52:32.274 --> 00:52:34.401
Okay. I'm ready to say it.

541
00:52:35.152 --> 00:52:36.528
My wish…

542
00:52:36.611 --> 00:52:39.948
is for you to be my dad. Ren.

543
00:53:07.684 --> 00:53:09.269
Kyoko!

544
00:53:11.146 --> 00:53:12.397
Kyoko!

545
00:53:37.422 --> 00:53:38.465
Thank you!

546
00:55:12.309 --> 00:55:15.437
Many mysteries unsolved
in the case of the Human Vapor.

547
00:55:15.520 --> 00:55:16.604
ONE YEAR LATER

548
00:55:16.688 --> 00:55:19.232
New information has emerged
regarding a connection between him

549
00:55:19.316 --> 00:55:20.984
and former reporter Kyoko Kono.

550
00:55:21.943 --> 00:55:24.696
Witnesses have revealed
that the two individuals in question

551
00:55:24.779 --> 00:55:27.741
were forced into illegal labor
at White Center.

552
00:55:27.824 --> 00:55:29.993
and they both lived there
during the same period.

553
00:55:30.076 --> 00:55:33.955
This suggests they knew each other
before the Human Vapor attacks began.

554
00:55:34.456 --> 00:55:37.208
To this day.
their whereabouts remain unknown.

555
00:55:37.792 --> 00:55:39.419
According to sources. one year ago.

556
00:55:39.502 --> 00:55:42.797
an officer and from the Metropolitan
Police Department witnessed the moment

557
00:55:42.881 --> 00:55:45.800
Kono the Human Vapor seemingly vanished.

558
00:55:45.884 --> 00:55:48.261
This strange occurrence took place
inside a vault

559
00:55:48.345 --> 00:55:50.930
in the basement of the old JNT building.

560
00:55:51.014 --> 00:55:53.850
Police believe the two
may have disappeared intentionally

561
00:55:53.933 --> 00:55:55.852
in order to avoid arrest.

562
00:55:58.355 --> 00:56:00.565
This is. uh… Who are you?

563
00:56:01.066 --> 00:56:04.444
Tatsuya Nishiyama. I'm from JNT.

564
00:56:04.944 --> 00:56:06.529
Right. Yes.

565
00:56:07.572 --> 00:56:09.824
So. how can I help you?

566
00:56:10.325 --> 00:56:14.621
It's a request from the PR office.
looking to do a piece on what we do here.

567
00:56:14.704 --> 00:56:16.998
It's for Police 24 Hours or something.

568
00:56:18.041 --> 00:56:19.667
You're doing a stakeout. right?

569
00:56:20.168 --> 00:56:22.587
Go along with her.
Feel free to ask whatever you want.

570
00:56:22.670 --> 00:56:24.547
Uh. hold on. Chief?

571
00:56:27.717 --> 00:56:29.052
Good to see you again.

572
00:56:30.470 --> 00:56:31.346
What?

573
00:56:32.180 --> 00:56:33.723
Have we met before?

574
00:56:33.807 --> 00:56:36.434
Yeah. a long time ago.

575
00:56:36.518 --> 00:56:38.603
We were working on the Human Vapor.

576
00:56:39.437 --> 00:56:41.356
Huh? Wait.

577
00:56:41.439 --> 00:56:43.817
In the parking lot? In Shizuoka?

578
00:56:43.900 --> 00:56:45.860
That's the one. You got it.

579
00:56:49.406 --> 00:56:52.033
-Okay. Shall we head out?
-Sure.

580
00:56:53.243 --> 00:56:54.244
Wow.

581
00:56:56.246 --> 00:56:57.664
Seriously.

582
00:57:00.125 --> 00:57:02.043
Last year was a lot. wasn't it?

583
00:57:04.462 --> 00:57:05.880
It sure was. yeah.

584
00:57:06.506 --> 00:57:08.007
Could've done with less.

585
00:57:11.136 --> 00:57:15.181
Welcome to horror paradise!
Let's go.

586
00:57:15.682 --> 00:57:19.686
How are all you killers doing tonight?
Bloody awesome?

587
00:57:20.186 --> 00:57:23.690
I can't even believe
what I'm seeing.

588
00:57:23.773 --> 00:57:25.650
We are now at ten

589
00:57:26.401 --> 00:57:28.194
million subscribers!

590
00:57:29.779 --> 00:57:31.281
Yay!

591
00:57:31.364 --> 00:57:34.159
Hey. Fujita. did you hear the news?

592
00:57:34.659 --> 00:57:35.702
We did it.

593
00:57:36.202 --> 00:57:38.079
We got here in one year.

594
00:57:39.038 --> 00:57:42.459
It's wild. hmm? But you know what?

595
00:57:43.918 --> 00:57:45.170
We're not finished yet!

596
00:57:45.253 --> 00:57:48.089
Killers. you need to know something
about my brother. okay?

597
00:57:48.173 --> 00:57:50.967
Fujita wanted to become
the world's number one streamer.

598
00:57:51.050 --> 00:57:52.218
That was his dream.

599
00:57:52.719 --> 00:57:55.805
I'm sorry to say he's threatened
to haunt us if you don't subscribe.

600
00:57:55.889 --> 00:57:59.392
So make sure you follow to join
Fujita and Kaho's Terror Zone.

601
00:57:59.476 --> 00:58:01.561
and don't forget to ring that bell
while you're at it!

602
00:58:01.644 --> 00:58:04.063
Because if you don't support us.

603
00:58:04.147 --> 00:58:08.485
then the spirit of the man himself
will haunt you!

604
00:58:12.906 --> 00:58:15.992
Illuminati! How did you find us?

605
00:58:16.075 --> 00:58:18.328
I'm so sorry. killers.
but that's it for today.

606
00:58:19.579 --> 00:58:22.332
"I'm here. my sister!"

607
00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:27.712
No! Stop!
Get out of my head! No. no! Stop!

608
00:58:27.795 --> 00:58:30.340
"Kaho. I still have so much to say!
Don't go!"

609
00:58:30.423 --> 00:58:32.800
Get out of my head! Stop! No!

610
